question: Did AA Limited report any changes to its capital structure? If there is no mention, return False.
raw: Yes, AA Limited reported changes to its capital structure. According to the notes to the consolidated financial statements, following the acquisition of the Group in March 2021, the proceeds of the £280m Class B3 Notes issued in January 2021 were released from escrow and combined with an equity contribution of £261m from Bidco in order to prepay and redeem the Class B2 Notes. In addition, £29m aggregate principal amount of Class B2 Notes which were held by AA Limited were surrendered for cancellation. As a result, all £570m of outstanding Class B2 Notes were redeemed as part of this refinancing. The Group also entered into a new £150m Senior Term Facility which it drew down immediately and used, in combination with £50m of cash, to refinance its existing £200m Senior Term Facility. Alongside this, the Group agreed a new £160m Liquidity Facility which remains undrawn and cancelled its existing Liquidity Facility of £165m.
